         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... distraction ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... honourable ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... therefore this ... divine ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (s)he spreads it. Thus ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... of the (Buddha worth ?) ... within long ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... very much (?) ... the monastic way ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... garments [and] ornaments ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... firmness among apsarases ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Īśvaradatta the excellent (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... says, «Honourable one, ...»</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... away ... she ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">The name b4 <hi>iśva(radatte)</hi> suggests appurtenance to the manuscript A 144-211, where it is attested in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a159"/> a3, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a160"/> b1, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a161"/> b4, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a164"/> a5, b4 and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht1150"/> a3.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">: The word division is uncertain.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><hi>knāṣ-äṃ</hi>: the correct interpretation of this form was given by <bibl><title corresp="ref:itkin2011"/><citedRange>251</citedRange></bibl>, to which a reference is unfortunately lacking in <bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2011"/><citedRange>45</citedRange></bibl> (which appeared later). Pace <bibl><title corresp="ref:malzahn2011b"/><citedRange>140</citedRange></bibl>, the form is not related to <hi>knā-</hi> 'know' (it is left with a question mark in <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>170a</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#a6" type="philcomment"><hi>(puttiśpa)rṣṣāṃ</hi>: Other restorations are also possible. Unlike in this case, would usually expect a noun to be following this obl.sg.f. adjective.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment"><hi>(wāk)m(a)ts</hi>: Other restorations are also possible.</note></p>
         </div>
